The**Product Added to Cart**trigger initiates a flow when a customer adds a product to their shopping cart. This trigger is often used to track shopping behavior and automate follow-up actions, such as abandoned cart reminders or personalized product recommendations.

<Note>
  **Note:** This Trigger is a part of
  [BigCommerce](https://support.salesmate.io/hc/en-us/articles/6774740880153-Introduction-and-Installation-of-BigCommerce)
  Integration
</Note>

**Topics Covered:**

- [How to Configure Product Added to Cart Trigger](https://support.salesmate.io/hc/en-us/articles/37780108171033-Product-Added-to-Cart#h_01J87MQBX3ZAPMX73WYYDNZPNR)

- [Practical Example](https://support.salesmate.io/hc/en-us/articles/37780108171033-Product-Added-to-Cart#h_01J8H3KW1E5N01AYAP56X0K278)

### How to Configure Product Added to Cart Trigger

- While creating the Trigger Based Flows select**Product Added to Cart**trigger

![](./Product Added to Cart – Salesmate_files/mceclip0.png)

- When setting up the**Product Added to Cart**trigger, you will configure the following:

  **\*Name:**Provide a descriptive name.
  **\*Description:**Briefly explain the purpose of the trigger.
  **\*Select Store:**Choose the BigCommerce store where the cart activity occurs.
  **\*Contact:**Specify conditions related to customer details.
  **\*BigCommerce:**Set conditions based on product-related properties that must be met before the trigger is activated.

- Hit the**Save**button to save the configuration and start making the flow.

![](./Product Added to Cart – Salesmate_files/mceclip1.png)

### Practical Example

Let's create a Smart Flow about when your contact whose Type = Customer adds a product to their cart, and the cart value reaches a certain amount, we will send out an email to a customer after a couple of hours saying the cart looks good and it's time to make a purchase. If the cart value remains the same for a selected period of time we can send out a reminder email and so on.
